    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I've investigated the issue a little bit deeper and haven't found any solution which does not require calls to OS native methods.\r\n\r\nThe current solution, based on the [window color heuristic algorithm](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/8685ad92c9ac9377ca75480c12d6c3a238148d38/ui/main.qml#L199-L207) works fine for macOS (and Windows?) but not for Linux (GNOME) - `window.hslLightness` doesn't change together with system theme. I've also noticed that `changeThemeFromOutside` is not triggered because neither of the observed events from `OSThemeEvent::eventFilter` is captured.\r\n\r\nQt is currently working on a cross-platform deterministic solution: https://bugreports.qt.io/browse/QTBUG-97910 which will be probably delivered in some upcoming Qt6 releases.\r\n\r\n---\r\n@saledjenic as you were the one working on the current solution, maybe you have some other ideas on how to work around the problem until Qt provides the solution?\r\n\r\n",
